# HockeyGame Project Overview

This repository is a custom C++ hockey game and engine project.

The goal is to build a high-quality real-time 4v4 hockey game.

Game design:

- 2 teams.
- 3 skaters + 1 goalie per team.
- 8 players total.
- 1 puck.
- 2 goals.
- Dedicated authoritative server.
- Clients send input.
- Server simulates authoritative state.
- Clients receive snapshots.
- Client prediction/interpolation/reconciliation will be used later.

Long-term engine systems:

- Vulkan renderer.
- SDL3 platform/window/input layer.
- Unity-style map editor.
- Entity Component System.
- Dedicated server.
- GameNetworkingSockets networking.
- Asset pipeline.
- Physics system.
- Hockey gameplay simulation.
- Cross-platform Windows/Linux support.

Target apps:

- `HockeyGameClient`: playable game client.
- `HockeyMapEditor`: Unity-style map editor.
- `HockeyDedicatedServer`: headless authoritative server.
- `HockeyCoreTests`: foundation/core tests.

Primary libraries:

- `libs/core`: platform, logging, config, paths, input, windowing, jobs, timing.
- `libs/ecs`: entity/component/scene/prefab data.
- `libs/assets`: asset loading/import/cooking.
- `libs/renderer`: Vulkan renderer using Volk and Vulkan Memory Allocator.
- `libs/physics`: physics integration.
- `libs/networking`: GameNetworkingSockets wrapper, protocol, lobbies, replication.
- `libs/gameplay`: hockey simulation/rules.
- `libs/editor`: editor panels/tools.

Development is phase-based.

Do not implement systems from future phases unless explicitly asked.
Do not create monolithic code.
Keep systems separated by library.
